cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.RO, cs.MM, cs.AI 

The paper deals with computer vision and image processing techniques, specifically depth super-resolution and photometric stereo. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves 3D reconstruction and robotics, which could fall under cs.GR (Graphics) and cs.RO (Robotics and Control). Additionally, the use of a variational framework and PDE-based regularizer suggests a focus on mathematical modeling and optimization, which could place the paper in cs.MM (Multimedia) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
